About
At Wine at the Docks, owner Patti Bryant is passionate about creating an atmosphere where wine enthusiasts, friends, and the community come together to savor life's simple pleasures. The journey began at the sponge docks in Tarpon Springs, and we've opened a second location in Downtown Dunedin.
We're all about bringing the good vibes and great wines to your glass. Our specialty is creating a chill, no-fuss spot where you can kick back and explore a wide range of fantastic wines from across the globe and around the corner. We're here to make your wine journey as relaxed and enjoyable as possible. So, whether you're a seasoned wine connoisseur or just looking for a fun night out, we've got the wine adventure you're looking for.
Our specialty wines are curated both locally and across the globe. Our homemade sangrias change weekly and are passionately crafted by Patti. And yes—locally crafted beers are always on tap.
At Wine at the Docks, we're on a mission to celebrate the world of wine and friendship, one glass at a time. Join us on this delightful journey of discovery, relaxation, and the simple pleasure of sharing a great bottle of wine.
We look forward to you becoming one of our regulars!
